      "sourceUrl": "https://leetcode.cn/problems/uncrossed-lines/description/",
      "code": "class Solution {\npublic:\n    int maxUncrossedLines(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {\n        int firstSize = nums1.size();\n        int secondSize = nums2.size();\n        vector<int> dp(secondSize + 1, 0);\n\n        for (int i = 1; i <= firstSize; ++i) {\n            int prevDiagonal = 0;\n\n            for (int j = 1; j <= secondSize; ++j) {\n                int oldAbove = dp[j];\n\n                if (nums1[i - 1] == nums2[j - 1]) {\n                    // prevDiagonal is the old dp[i - 1][j - 1].\n                    dp[j] = prevDiagonal + 1;\n                } else {\n                    // dp[j] is old above, and dp[j - 1] is current left.\n                    dp[j] = max(dp[j], dp[j - 1]);\n                }\n\n                prevDiagonal = oldAbove;\n            }\n        }\n\n        return dp[secondSize];\n    }\n};"
