      "code": "class Solution {\npublic:\n    int maxSubarraySumCircular(vector<int>& nums) {\n        int totalSum = nums[firstIndex];\n        int maxEndingHere = nums[firstIndex];\n        int minEndingHere = nums[firstIndex];\n        int maxSubarraySum = nums[firstIndex];\n        int minSubarraySum = nums[firstIndex];\n\n        for (int index = firstIndex + indexStep;\n             index < static_cast<int>(nums.size()); ++index) {\n            int value = nums[index];\n            totalSum += value;\n\n            // maxEndingHere is the best non-empty subarray that must end at\n            // the current index: either start here or extend the previous one.\n            maxEndingHere = max(value, maxEndingHere + value);\n            maxSubarraySum = max(maxSubarraySum, maxEndingHere);\n\n            // For a circular answer, the skipped middle part should be as\n            // small as possible, so we run the same idea with min instead.\n            minEndingHere = min(value, minEndingHere + value);\n            minSubarraySum = min(minSubarraySum, minEndingHere);\n        }\n\n        if (totalSum == minSubarraySum) {\n            // Removing the whole array would leave an empty subarray, which\n            // the problem forbids. This also covers the one-element case.\n            return maxSubarraySum;\n        }\n\n        int circularSubarraySum = totalSum - minSubarraySum;\n        return max(maxSubarraySum, circularSubarraySum);\n    }\n\nprivate:\n    static constexpr int firstIndex = 0;\n    static constexpr int indexStep = 1;\n};"
